# Bump version before retry

When plugin changes are ready for Beth to reload in Lightroom and retry (publish, export, audit, etc.):

1. **Bump `revision`** in `before-and-after.lrdevplugin/Info.lua` (keep `major`/`minor` unless the change warrants it)
2. Update `display` to match (e.g. `0.9.0` → `0.9.1`)
3. Tell Beth the new version and remind her to reload in Plug-in Manager

`PluginInit.lua` logs the version on init. Beth verifies reload via `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/Lightroom/lrc_console.log`:

```
Before and After VERSION 0.9.1 (0.9.1)
```

If the log still shows the old version, LR didn't pick up the changes.

## Version scheme

- **`revision`** — increment for each test/retry cycle during active dev
- **`minor`** — feature additions or meaningful behavior changes
- **`major`** — breaking changes (rare)

Do this as the **last step** before saying "reload and retry" — not on every intermediate edit.

## Example

```lua
-- 0.9.0 → 0.9.1
VERSION = { major = 0, minor = 9, revision = 1, display = "0.9.1" },
```
